            <title>[LU-8352] Mellanox/OFED build breakage due to file_inode macro.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8352</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The patch landed for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8176&quot; title=&quot;Add file_dentry and file_inode wrappers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8176&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8176&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced support for file_inode() wrapper from upstream. The problem is that the OFED/Mellanox stack does the same thing which causes a collision that will prevent lustre from building.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Latest Lustre 2.8.55 built against an OFED or Mellanox stack.</environment>
